com.biorecorder.edflib.util

Class EndianBitConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biorecorder.edflib.util.EndianBitConverter

  • public class EndianBitConverter
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains several useful static methods to convert Java integer (32-bit, signed, BIG_ENDIAN) to an array of bytes (BIG_ENDIAN or LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered) and vice versa

      • intToLittleEndianBytes

        public static byte[] intToLittleEndianBytes(int value,
                                            int resultantNumberOfBytes)
        Convert BIG_ENDIAN java int to LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered byte array. Resultant array will contain specified number of bytes: 4, 3, 2 or 1.

        3 bytes LITTLE_ENDIAN data format is used to write/read BDF files
        2 bytes LITTLE_ENDIAN data format is used to write/read EDF files

        Parameters:
        value - the value to be converted to byte array, standard 32-bit signed java int (BIG_ENDIAN)
        resultantNumberOfBytes - number of bytes in resultant array. Can be: 4, 3, 2 or 1.
        Returns:
        resultant byte array (LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered)

      • littleEndianBytesToInt

        public static int littleEndianBytesToInt(byte... bytes)
        Convert given LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered bytes to BIG_ENDIAN java integer. Available number of input bytes: 4, 3, 2 or 1.
        Parameters:
        bytes - 4, 3, 2 or 1 bytes (LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered) to be converted to int
        Returns:
        standard 32-bit signed java int (BIG_ENDIAN)

      • littleEndianBytesToInt

        public static int littleEndianBytesToInt(byte[] byteArray,
                                         int offset,
                                         int numberOfBytesPerInt)
        Convert specified number of bytes (4, 3, 2 or 1) of the LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered byte array to BIG_ENDIAN java integer. Сonversion begins from the specified offset position.
        Parameters:
        byteArray - byte array (LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered) from which 4, 3, 2 or 1 bytes are taken to be converted to int
        numberOfBytesPerInt - number of bytes that should be converted to int. Can be: 4, 3, 2 or 1.
        offset - the offset within the array of the first byte to be converted
        Returns:
        standard 32-bit signed java int (BIG_ENDIAN)

      • littleEndianByteArrayToIntArray

        public static void littleEndianByteArrayToIntArray(byte[] byteArray,
                                                   int byteArrayOffset,
                                                   int[] intArray,
                                                   int intArrayOffset,
                                                   int lengthInInts,
                                                   int numberOfBytesPerInt)
        Convert specified number of elements from LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered byte array (starting from byteArrayOffset position) to ints and write resultant ints to the given int array (starting from intArrayOffset position)
        Parameters:
        byteArray - byte array (LITTLE_ENDIAN ordered) to be converted to int array
        byteArrayOffset - the offset within the byte array of the first byte to be converted
        intArray - int array to write resultant ints
        intArrayOffset - the offset within the int array of the first int to be written
        lengthInInts - number of resultant ints. Number of bytes that will be converted to ints = lengthInInts * numberOfBytesPerInt
        numberOfBytesPerInt - number of bytes converted to ONE int. Can be: 4, 3, 2 or 1.
